content:
Creating a website template with a navigation bar, header, content area, and footer using HTML5 and CSS3 involves structuring your HTML with semantic elements and styling them with CSS. Here's a basic example to get you started:

### HTML (index.html)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Website Template</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>My Website</h1>
    </header>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#services">Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    <main>
        <section id="home">
            <h2>Welcome to My Website</h2>
            <p>This is the content area where you can add your main content.</p>
        </section>
        <!-- Add more sections as needed -->
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 My Website. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (styles.css)

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 0;
    text-align: center;
}

nav {
    background-color: #444;
}

nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
}

nav ul li {
    margin: 0 15px;
}

nav ul li a {
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 10px 0;
    display: block;
}

nav ul li a:hover {
    border-bottom: 2px solid #fff;
}

main {
    padding: 20px;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 20px auto;
}

footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px 0;
    position: fixed;
    width: 100%;
    bottom: 0;
}
```

### Explanation:

- **HTML Structure**: The HTML uses semantic elements like `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, and `<footer>` to define the structure of the webpage.
- **CSS Styling**: Basic styles are applied to make the layout visually appealing. The navigation bar uses a flexbox layout to align the links horizontally. The footer is fixed at the bottom of the page.
- **Responsive Design**: The viewport meta tag and the use of flexible units in CSS help ensure the layout is responsive.

Feel free to expand this template by adding more sections, styles, and functionalities as needed for your specific project.
